 Religion Day lies in its message of unity. Despite the diversity of beliefs, traditions, and practices, all religions aim to nurture values like compassion, justice, and the betterment of society. By fostering dialogue and mutual respect, World Religion Day encourages communities to focus on what binds them rather than divides them. In 2025, the theme is expected to echo these values, emphasising the harmony that arises from embracing diversity.
